      <h2>Background: Making a Protein</h2>
      <p>Genes that provide instructions for proteins are expressed in a two-step process.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>In transcription, the DNA sequence of a gene is "rewritten" in RNA. In eukaryotes, the RNA must go through additional processing steps to become a messenger RNA, or mRNA.</li>
        <li>In translation, the sequence of nucleotides in the mRNA is "translated" into a sequence of amino acids in a polypeptide (protein chain).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
