        <h2>Dominant and Recessive Genes</h2>
        <p>Inside the DNA molecule are sections of information called genes. Each gene tells the cell how to make a certain protein which may determine a trait such as the color of the eyes. Each gene is made of a series of nucleic acids built by codons.</p>
        <p>Each creatre inherits two genes for each trait from their parents. Some genes are more dominant than others. For example, green eyes are dominant over purple eyes. If a creature has a green eye gene and a purple eye gene, they will have green eyes. They will only have purple eyes if both genes are purple.</p>
        <p>The green eye gene is called the dominant gene and the purple eye gene is the recessive gene.</p>
        <p>A Punnet Square, as shown here, is a common way to figure out the pattern of inheritance.  A Punnet Square shows all the possible combinations of genes from the parents.</p>
